---
import Layout from '@layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="With Agents — Practical coding-agent workflows">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-24">
    <section class="space-y-8">
      <p class="text-sm font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-indigo-600">
        Durable context for coding agents
      </p>
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-light leading-tight text-gray-950">
          Make your repo the memory.
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-gray-600 font-light leading-relaxed max-w-3xl">
          With Agents is a working collection about agentic coding. The public article focuses on durable repo-local context; the older practice-path posts are being refreshed as drafts against the current state of coding agents.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4">
        <a href="/posts/durable-context-coding-agents" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-gray-900 px-5 py-3 text-white transition-colors duration-200 hover:bg-gray-700 focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-indigo-600/50 focus-visible:ring-offset-2">
          Read the article
        </a>
        <a href="/resources/coding-with-agents" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-lg border border-gray-300 px-5 py-3 text-gray-800 transition-colors duration-200 hover:border-gray-400 hover:bg-gray-50 focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-indigo-600/50 focus-visible:ring-offset-2">
          Browse resources
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-3">
      <a href="/posts/durable-context-coding-agents" class="rounded-xl border border-gray-200 bg-white p-6 transition-all duration-200 hover:border-gray-300 hover:shadow-lg focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-indigo-600/50 focus-visible:ring-offset-2">
        <p class="mb-3 text-sm font-medium uppercase tracking-wide text-indigo-600">Current article</p>
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-2xl font-light text-gray-900">Your Repo Is the Memory</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">A field guide for keeping coding agents aligned with repo-local truth, shared state, proof, and human judgment.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/posts/durable-context-coding-agents/slides" class="rounded-xl border border-gray-200 bg-white p-6 transition-all duration-200 hover:border-gray-300 hover:shadow-lg focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-indigo-600/50 focus-visible:ring-offset-2">
        <p class="mb-3 text-sm font-medium uppercase tracking-wide text-indigo-600">Presentation base</p>
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-2xl font-light text-gray-900">View the slide draft</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">The article is structured as a 12-section deck base for a later visual, less-text presentation pass.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/resources/coding-with-agents" class="rounded-xl border border-gray-200 bg-white p-6 transition-all duration-200 hover:border-gray-300 hover:shadow-lg focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-indigo-600/50 focus-visible:ring-offset-2">
        <p class="mb-3 text-sm font-medium uppercase tracking-wide text-indigo-600">Resource hub</p>
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-2xl font-light text-gray-900">Curated talks and summaries</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">Podcasts, videos, and articles with notes you can scan before watching.</p>
      </a>
    </section>

    <section class="rounded-2xl bg-slate-50 p-8 md:p-10">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-light text-gray-900 mb-4">What is public now</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        For now, the public writing path is intentionally narrow: one article, one slide draft, and the resource library that feeds future revisions.
      </p>
      <ol class="space-y-3 text-gray-700">
        <li><a class="text-indigo-700 hover:text-indigo-500" href="/posts/durable-context-coding-agents">1. Read the durable-context article</a></li>
        <li><a class="text-indigo-700 hover:text-indigo-500" href="/posts/durable-context-coding-agents/slides">2. Preview the slide draft</a></li>
        <li><a class="text-indigo-700 hover:text-indigo-500" href="/resources/coding-with-agents">3. Browse the source talks, transcripts, and summaries</a></li>
      </ol>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>
